AB  - The task of managing natural resources can be described as complex, unstructured, having multiple and conflicting criteria, and involving decisions by groups with diverging interests. Several sources in literature have shown group decision support systems (GDSS) to be successful in improving decision making efforts in problems similar to the management of natural resources. This paper discusses the application and benefits of using a GDSS in the management of a natural resource.
