AB  - An integrated knowledge-based spatial decision support system, Landassess DSS, is being developed to assist with the sustainable management of Australia's northern grazing lands. The system incorporates a knowledge base of management and ecological knowledge, a natural resource database, a geographic information system, and scientific and economic models. The system requirements introduced the need for an integrating paradigm to facilitate the modeling of the natural resource system, knowledge representation, representation of heterogeneous data, and the integration of system components. The ability to model real-world features with corresponding knowledge base and software objects, which include structural and behavioral information, provides a powerful and intuitive method for representing and integrating knowledge and data, process models, and spatial information, as well as encapsulating and abstracting different levels of information and functionality.
