AB  - Environmental reservation and the use of natural resources have gained paramount importance worldwide during the past two decades. This increased attention emanates from the fact that natural resources are being deployed, degraded and exhausted and that environmental damage is becoming global in context and scale to warrant the attention of decisionmakers. Within this context, the challenge that faces natural resources managers in developing countries in particular is the allocation of the scarce resources among the different users within the domain of increased scarcity and demand bearing into account the requirements for environmental conservation and safety. DSSs are found to be- as integrated control tools- helpful in providing the necessary decision support.
