AB  - This chapter provides an overview of web-based decision-support systems (DSS) that are seeing a widespread use among decision makers, educators, and researchers in various disciplines and domains: business, natural resource management, medicine, manufacturing, engineering, and many others. The chapter opens with an introduction to DSS, complex systems, and decision theory. It then proceeds to discuss the design of web-enabled DSS and back-end database systems. Next, it addresses the front-end user interface and the intermediate application-layer concepts. In addition, the chapter also covers the topics related to interfacing the model base. The chapter concludes with one important application of DSS in higher education-DSS for management simulation games and a discussion of the future evolution of web-based DSS.
