AB  - Fort A.P. hill is a 76,000-acre Army training installation located in the Coastal Plain of Virginia. The Forestry Section is developing a GIS based Decision Support System (DSS) that uses Ecosystem Management guidelines to develop stand prescriptions and plan forestry activities to achieve desired military training objectives. The development and implementation of the DSS involved the entire Fort A. P. Hill Environmental and Natural Resources team. This team consists of personnel from endangered and threatened species management, wildlife and fisheries management, erosion control, cultural resources, forestry, and military training through the Integrated Training Area Management program. The problem of spatially distributing forest stand prescriptions to achieve a wide variety of objectives, that at times compete with each other, is being addressed by utilizing the DSS. This system is a tool that will analyze forest management options with the goal to conserve and enhance biological diversity while maintaining sustainable forest resources and most importantly to conserve and improve the environment in support of the military training mission.
