AB  - The operation mode of traditional remote sensing satellite is passive. The satellite passively carries out environmental awareness and task implementation after receiving ground instructions, and lacks the ability of autonomous operation and decision-making.In order to improve the intelligent level of remote sensing satellites, a fire detection method for forest and grassland fires is proposed, and a set of fire detection system through infrared imaging is designed. Infrared spectrum imaging results are processed in orbit, and fire information, such as location and area, is obtained in real time. Then the fire information is transmitted to the ground user through the BeiDou transimission channel in China, for users of forestry, natural resources, emergency management and other relevant departments to respond quickly and provide decision support.The fire detection system scheme has a high timeliness of disaster emergency response capability and can solve the time delay problem of disaster emergency response. The system can provide accurate forest fire location, area, shape and other information, and achieve real-time, autonomous, multifunctional and intelligent detection of fire targets in orbit. The fire detection system was launched into orbit on August 4, 2022, with China's first terrestrial ecosystem carbon monitoring satellite, "Goumang". Compared with the traditional way of remote sensing satellite returning images to the ground station, this system can obtain disaster information 3 to 4 hours in advance, leaving more ample response time for the users.
