AB  - Wild edible plants (WEPs) are important in ethnobiological research in India. Maharashtra has been chosen as a case study to understand the state of knowledge about WEPs and their use for sustaina-ble development. A total of 436 edible plants have been listed so far, but documentation of manage-ment practices is less and needs systematic research in the future. We suggest future action research themes and a decision -support framework for using WEPs in Maharashtra.
