TI  - Forest Information Modeling: A Novel Approach to Sustainable Forest Management
T2  - EAI ENDORSED TRANSACTIONS ON SCALABLE INFORMATION SYSTEMS
LA  - English
KW  - Forest Information Modeling
KW  - Ecosystem Services
KW  - Smart Forestry
KW  - Forest 4.0
KW  - forest management
KW  - information systems
KW  - forest data analysis
KW  - REMOTE
AB  - This research introduces Forest Information Modeling (FIM) as an innovative approach to sustainable forest management. FIM is depicted as a comprehensive digital framework that integrates various data layers and technologies to enhance the efficiency, accuracy, and sustainability of forest management practices. Key components of FIM include ecological data collection, spatial representation, process modeling, decision support systems, and stakeholder engagement, all aimed at facilitating informed decision-making and efficient resource utilization. The study explores the theoretical underpinnings of FIM, its practical applications through case studies, and the construction of FIM using real-world datasets. Practical illustration using the Biomass tree data base is presented. The study addresses the challenges, potential impacts, and future directions of FIM in the context of global forest management and conservation efforts. The findings underscore FIM's potential to transform forest management practices by improving decision-making processes, promoting environmental sustainability, and fostering stakeholder collaboration.
